Extension 0..*ExtensionA medicinal product in the final form, suitable for administration - after any mixing of multiple components
Slices for extension 2..*ExtensionExtension
Slice: Unordered, Closed by value:url
extension:status ?!1..1Extensiondraft | active | retired | unknown
value[x] 0..1codedraft | active | retired | unknown
Binding: Cross-version VS for R5.PublicationStatus for use in FHIR R4 (required): The lifecycle status of an artifact.
extension:formOf 0..*ExtensionReferences a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product
value[x] 0..1Reference(MedicinalProductDefinition)References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product
extension:administrableDoseForm 0..1ExtensionThe dose form of the final product after necessary reconstitution or processing
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptThe dose form of the final product after necessary reconstitution or processing
Binding: administrable-dose-form (??) (example): Dose form for a medication, in the form suitable for administering to the patient, after mixing, where necessary.
extension:unitOfPresentation 0..1ExtensionThe presentation type in which this item is given to a patient. e.g. for a spray - 'puff'
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptThe presentation type in which this item is given to a patient. e.g. for a spray - 'puff'
Binding: unit-of-presentation (??) (example): The presentation type in which an administrable medicinal product is given to a patient.
extension:producedFrom 0..*ExtensionIndicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form
value[x] 0..1Reference(ManufacturedItemDefinition)Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form
extension:ingredient 0..*ExtensionThe ingredients of this administrable medicinal product. This is only needed if the ingredients are not specified either using ManufacturedItemDefiniton, or using by incoming references from the Ingredient resource
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptThe ingredients of this administrable medicinal product. This is only needed if the ingredients are not specified either using ManufacturedItemDefiniton, or using by incoming references from the Ingredient resource
Binding: substance-codes (??) (example): This value set includes all substance codes from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar value set.
extension:device 0..1ExtensionA device that is integral to the medicinal product, in effect being considered as an "ingredient" of the medicinal product
value[x] 0..1Reference(DeviceDefinition)A device that is integral to the medicinal product, in effect being considered as an "ingredient" of the medicinal product
extension:description 0..1ExtensionA general description of the product, when in its final form, suitable for administration e.g. effervescent blue liquid, to be swallowed
value[x] 0..1markdownA general description of the product, when in its final form, suitable for administration e.g. effervescent blue liquid, to be swallowed
extension:property 0..*ExtensionCharacteristics e.g. a product's onset of action
Slices for extension 1..*ExtensionExtension
Slice: Unordered, Closed by value:url
extension:type 1..1ExtensionA code expressing the type of characteristic
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptA code expressing the type of characteristic
Binding: product-characteristic-codes (??) (example): This value set includes all observable entity codes from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar value set.
extension:value[x] 0..1ExtensionA value for the characteristic
value[x] 0..1A value for the characteristic
valueCodeableConceptCodeableConcept
valueQuantityQuantity
valueDatedate
valueBooleanboolean
valueMarkdownmarkdown
valueAttachmentAttachment
valueReferenceReference(Binary)
extension:status 0..1ExtensionThe status of characteristic e.g. assigned or pending
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptThe status of characteristic e.g. assigned or pending
Binding: Cross-version VS for R5.PublicationStatus for use in FHIR R4 (required): The lifecycle status of an artifact.
extension:routeOfAdministration 1..*ExtensionThe path by which the product is taken into or makes contact with the body
Slices for extension 1..*ExtensionExtension
Slice: Unordered, Closed by value:url
extension:code 1..1ExtensionCoded expression for the route
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptCoded expression for the route
Binding: SNOMEDCTRouteCodes (example): A code specifying the route or physiological path of administration of a therapeutic agent into or onto a patient's body.
extension:firstDose 0..1ExtensionThe first dose (dose quantity) administered can be specified for the product
value[x] 0..1QuantityThe first dose (dose quantity) administered can be specified for the product
extension:maxSingleDose 0..1ExtensionThe maximum single dose that can be administered
value[x] 0..1QuantityThe maximum single dose that can be administered
extension:maxDosePerDay 0..1ExtensionThe maximum dose quantity to be administered in any one 24-h period
value[x] 0..1QuantityThe maximum dose quantity to be administered in any one 24-h period
extension:maxDosePerTreatmentPeriod 0..1ExtensionThe maximum dose per treatment period that can be administered
value[x] 0..1RatioThe maximum dose per treatment period that can be administered
extension:maxTreatmentPeriod 0..1ExtensionThe maximum treatment period during which the product can be administered
value[x] 0..1DurationThe maximum treatment period during which the product can be administered
extension:targetSpecies 0..*ExtensionA species for which this route applies
Slices for extension 1..*ExtensionExtension
Slice: Unordered, Closed by value:url
extension:code 1..1ExtensionCoded expression for the species
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptCoded expression for the species
Binding: target-species (??) (example): A tissue type of an animal.
extension:withdrawalPeriod 0..*ExtensionA species specific time during which consumption of animal product is not appropriate
Slices for extension 2..*ExtensionExtension
Slice: Unordered, Closed by value:url
extension:tissue 1..1ExtensionThe type of tissue for which the withdrawal period applies, e.g. meat, milk
value[x] 0..1CodeableConceptThe type of tissue for which the withdrawal period applies, e.g. meat, milk
Binding: animal-tissue-type (??) (example): A tissue type of an animal.
extension:value 1..1ExtensionA value for the time
value[x] 0..1QuantityA value for the time
extension:supportingInformation 0..1ExtensionExtra information about the withdrawal period
value[x] 0..1stringExtra information about the withdrawal period
url 1..1uri"http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-AdministrableProductDefinition"

element.short: References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product
element.definition: References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product.  If this administrable product describes the administration of a crushed tablet, the 'formOf' would be the product representing a distribution containing tablets and possibly also a cream.  This is distinct from the 'producedFrom' which refers to the specific components of the product that are used in this preparation, rather than the product as a whole.

element.short: Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form
element.definition: Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form.  In some cases, an administrable form might use all of the items from the overall product (or there might only be one item), while in other cases, an administrable form might use only a subset of the items available in the overall product.  For example, an administrable form might involve combining a liquid and a powder available as part of an overall product, but not involve applying the also supplied cream.

element.short: A medicinal product in the final form, suitable for administration - after any mixing of multiple components
element.definition: A medicinal product in the final form which is suitable for administering to a patient (after any mixing of multiple components, dissolution etc. has been performed).

element.short: draft | active | retired | unknown
element.definition: The status of this administrable product. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.
element.isModifierReason: This is labeled as "Is Modifier" because applications should not use a retired {{title}} without due consideration

element.short: draft | active | retired | unknown
element.definition: The status of this administrable product. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content.

binding.description: The lifecycle status of an artifact.

element.short: References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product
element.definition: References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product.  If this administrable product describes the administration of a crushed tablet, the 'formOf' would be the product representing a distribution containing tablets and possibly also a cream.  This is distinct from the 'producedFrom' which refers to the specific components of the product that are used in this preparation, rather than the product as a whole.

element.short: References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product
element.definition: References a product from which one or more of the constituent parts of that product can be prepared and used as described by this administrable product.  If this administrable product describes the administration of a crushed tablet, the 'formOf' would be the product representing a distribution containing tablets and possibly also a cream.  This is distinct from the 'producedFrom' which refers to the specific components of the product that are used in this preparation, rather than the product as a whole.

element.short: The dose form of the final product after necessary reconstitution or processing
element.definition: The dose form of the final product after necessary reconstitution or processing. Contrasts to the manufactured dose form (see ManufacturedItemDefinition). If the manufactured form was 'powder for solution for injection', the administrable dose form could be 'solution for injection' (once mixed with another item having manufactured form 'solvent for solution for injection').

element.short: The dose form of the final product after necessary reconstitution or processing
element.definition: The dose form of the final product after necessary reconstitution or processing. Contrasts to the manufactured dose form (see ManufacturedItemDefinition). If the manufactured form was 'powder for solution for injection', the administrable dose form could be 'solution for injection' (once mixed with another item having manufactured form 'solvent for solution for injection').

binding.description: Dose form for a medication, in the form suitable for administering to the patient, after mixing, where necessary.

element.short: The presentation type in which this item is given to a patient. e.g. for a spray - 'puff'
element.definition: The presentation type in which this item is given to a patient. e.g. for a spray - 'puff' (as in 'contains 100 mcg per puff'), or for a liquid - 'vial' (as in 'contains 5 ml per vial').

element.short: The presentation type in which this item is given to a patient. e.g. for a spray - 'puff'
element.definition: The presentation type in which this item is given to a patient. e.g. for a spray - 'puff' (as in 'contains 100 mcg per puff'), or for a liquid - 'vial' (as in 'contains 5 ml per vial').

binding.description: The presentation type in which an administrable medicinal product is given to a patient.

element.short: Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form
element.definition: Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form.  In some cases, an administrable form might use all of the items from the overall product (or there might only be one item), while in other cases, an administrable form might use only a subset of the items available in the overall product.  For example, an administrable form might involve combining a liquid and a powder available as part of an overall product, but not involve applying the also supplied cream.

element.short: Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form
element.definition: Indicates the specific manufactured items that are part of the 'formOf' product that are used in the preparation of this specific administrable form.  In some cases, an administrable form might use all of the items from the overall product (or there might only be one item), while in other cases, an administrable form might use only a subset of the items available in the overall product.  For example, an administrable form might involve combining a liquid and a powder available as part of an overall product, but not involve applying the also supplied cream.

element.short: The ingredients of this administrable medicinal product. This is only needed if the ingredients are not specified either using ManufacturedItemDefiniton, or using by incoming references from the Ingredient resource
element.definition: The ingredients of this administrable medicinal product. This is only needed if the ingredients are not specified either using ManufacturedItemDefiniton (via AdministrableProductDefinition.producedFrom) to state which component items are used to make this, or using by incoming references from the Ingredient resource, to state in detail which substances exist within this. This element allows a basic coded ingredient to be used.

element.short: The ingredients of this administrable medicinal product. This is only needed if the ingredients are not specified either using ManufacturedItemDefiniton, or using by incoming references from the Ingredient resource
element.definition: The ingredients of this administrable medicinal product. This is only needed if the ingredients are not specified either using ManufacturedItemDefiniton (via AdministrableProductDefinition.producedFrom) to state which component items are used to make this, or using by incoming references from the Ingredient resource, to state in detail which substances exist within this. This element allows a basic coded ingredient to be used.

binding.description: This value set includes all substance codes from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar value set.
